50|$|Although {{similar in}} {{finished}} appearance to the double bowline, the water bowline is formed with a <b>clove</b> <b>hitch</b> as the loop in the standing {{part of the}} rope. This {{is similar to the}} double bowline, which puts the running end through a round turn. The additional friction from the <b>clove</b> <b>hitch</b> increases the security of this knot.|$|R
